# Repository-root .dockerignore.
#
# Every per-stack Dockerfile in this repo (app/{api,auth,web}/Dockerfile)
# already sets its own build context to its own stack directory (see
# compose.yml's build.context) and carries its own app/<stack>/.dockerignore,
# so this root file has no effect on those builds.
#
# app/migrator/Dockerfile is the one exception: its build context is the
# *repository root* (see that Dockerfile's header comment), because it also
# COPYs app/api/db/migrations and app/auth/db/migrations, which live outside
# app/migrator's own directory tree:
#
#   docker build -f app/migrator/Dockerfile .
#
# Without this file, that build sends the *entire* repository -- including
# .git/ (packfile history) and app/iac/envs/dev/.terraform/ (provider
# binaries) -- to the Docker daemon as build context on every invocation,
# even though the Dockerfile's own COPY instructions only ever read
# app/migrator/** and app/{api,auth}/db/migrations/**. None of the patterns
# below match those two needed paths.

# Version control metadata (never needed to build any image)
.git
.github

# Terraform local working directories / state (see app/iac/.gitignore).
# app/iac/envs/dev/.terraform alone is hundreds of MB of provider binaries
# and plugin caches, none of which any app/* Dockerfile ever reads.
**/.terraform/
*.tfstate
*.tfstate.*

# Secrets / local env overrides -- never intended for a build context
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# JS package manager output (large; only app/web's own build reads it, via
# bun install inside app/web's own Dockerfile build stage, never via a COPY
# from the repository root)
**/node_modules/

# Editor / OS cruft
.vscode
**/.DS_Store

# Docs and non-build metadata
*.md
docs/
